# Morse Micro HaLow Driver for Ubuntu/Tachyon - License Information

This repository contains components from multiple sources with different licenses.
Each component retains its original license.

## Repository Structure and Licensing

| Directory | License | Copyright |
|-----------|---------|-----------|
| `driver/morse_driver-1.16.4/` | GPLv2 | Morse Micro |
| `tools/morsecli/` | GPLv2 | Morse Micro |
| `tools/wpa_supplicant_s1g/` | BSD-3-Clause | Jouni Malinen, Morse Micro |
| `firmware/` | Morse Micro Binary Distribution License | Morse Micro |
| `patches/` | GPLv2 | Morse Micro (via morse-feed) |
| `driver/Makefile.ubuntu` | MIT | Dusty Robotics |
| Documentation (*.md) | MIT | Dusty Robotics |

## License Details

### GPLv2 Components (driver, morsecli, patches)

The morse_driver, morse_cli, and patches are licensed under the GNU General
Public License version 2. Full license text is included in:
- `driver/morse_driver-1.16.4/LICENSE`
- `tools/morsecli/LICENSES/GPL-2.0-or-later.txt`

Source code is provided in full compliance with GPLv2 requirements.

### BSD-3-Clause (wpa_supplicant_s1g)

The wpa_supplicant_s1g component is licensed under the BSD 3-Clause License.
See `tools/wpa_supplicant_s1g/COPYING` for details.

### Morse Micro Binary Distribution License (firmware)

The firmware binary files in `firmware/` are licensed under the Morse Micro
Binary Distribution License. Key terms:

- Free to use with Morse Micro hardware products
- May be redistributed complete and unmodified
- Must be used solely with Morse Micro Wi-Fi HaLow chips
- No reverse engineering or modification permitted

Full license text is available in the upstream repository:
https://github.com/MorseMicro/morse-firmware

### MIT License (build system and documentation)

The build system adaptations (Makefile.ubuntu) and documentation created by
Dusty Robotics are licensed under MIT:

Copyright (c) 2024 Dusty Robotics

